            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Sum of P(0), P(1), P(2) using Binomial formula.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>If A and B are events such that P(A \cup B) = 3/4, P(A \cap B) = 1/4, P(A) = 2/3. Find P(B):</text>
            <option id="A">1/3</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>3/4 = 2/3 + P(B) - 1/4 -&gt; 3/4 + 1/4 - 2/3 = P(B) -&gt; 1 - 2/3 = 1/3.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>In probability distribution, p(x) = k/x for x=1,2,3. Find k:</text>
            <option id="A">6/11</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>k(1 + 1/2 + 1/3) = 1 -&gt; k(11/6) = 1 -&gt; k = 6/11.</explanation></question>
        <question>
