        <question>
            <text>A card from pack of 52 is lost. From remaining, 2 cards drawn are both diamonds. Prob lost card is diamond:</text>
            <option id="A">11/50</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Complex Bayes' application. Let E1 lost is dim, E2 not. A is 2 diam drawn. P(E1)=1/4, P(E2)=3/4. P(A|E1)=12C2/51C2. P(A|E2)=13C2/51C2. P(E1|A) = (1/4 * 66) / (1/4 * 66 + 3/4 * 78) = 66 / (66 + 234) = 66 / 300 = 11/50.</explanation></question>
