        <question>
            <text>A and B play game where A wins if he throws 6 first. Prob A wins if he starts:</text>
            <option id="A">6/11</option><option id="B">5/11</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>P + (5/6)(5/6)P = 1/6 -&gt; (1 + 25/36)P = 1/6 -&gt; 61/36 P = 1/6? No. P = 1/6 + (5/6)^2 P -&gt; P(1-25/36) = 1/6 -&gt; P(11/36) = 1/6 -&gt; P = 6/11.</explanation></question>
